    "narrative": "The optimizer for Ghost Ride the WHIP favors high-upside speed threats against Lance McCullers Jr. today, making **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (74.29) and **Giancarlo Stanton** (66.98) primary focal points. **James Wood** (75.23) leads the board as our top play; his batting lead-off spot against a middling arm like B. Hudson provides the highest projected floor, benefiting from an elite +10% order bonus. Meanwhile, **Mickey Moniak** (62.76) serves as a savvy start; despite facing a capable arm in F. Peralta, he benefits from a massive +14% platoon edge and a slow delivery from the mound, which significantly boosts his stolen base expectation\u2014a critical metric given our current scarcity in that category. **Trevor Story** (73.82) is also a strong play, though his upside is tempered by a 34% rain risk in his matchup against Young.\n\nThe tightest decision on the bench was **Seiya Suzuki** (44.34), who narrowly missed the cut. While he projects as a reliable bat, he was penalized by a -19% SP skill handicap against E. Sheehan and the optimizer's aggressive stance on prioritizing elite platoon advantages for our utility slots. We are also monitoring the lineup status of **Dalton Rushing** (54.84); while his score remains in the marginal tier, his platoon advantage against Taillon is essential for our C1 production. We continue to hold **Corbin Carroll** in reserve due to his team off-day, as we remain disciplined with our game caps to ensure we have the necessary depth for high-leverage matchups later in the week. **Josh Naylor** (67.84) and **Austin Riley** (62.28) anchor the middle of the order, providing the stability needed to balance the volatility of our speed-first strategy.",
